<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Solve the quadratic equation <m>{6 x^2-16 x+10}=0</m>. If there is a repeated root, enter this twice.</p>
<p>
    <nowrap><m>x = </m> <fillin characters="5" name="ans1"/>  or <m>x = </m> <fillin characters="5" name="ans2"/>
    </nowrap>
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><p>We are asked to factorise the quadratic equation <m>{6 x^2-16 x+10}=0.</m></p><p>First factorise the left-hand side:</p><p><me>{6 x^2-16 x+10}={\left(2 x-2\right) \left(3 x-5\right)}.</me></p><p>Equate each factor to zero to obtain the two solutions:</p><p>Solution 1: <m>x=<nbsp/>{1}.</m></p><p>Solution 2: <m>x= {\frac{5}{3}}.</m></p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>1</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>\frac{5}{3}</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>